course_metadata.title: Renovation of a typical residential building

content_chunks.content: The e-course serves as an introductory unit within a broader curriculum on sustainable construction and building modernization. It provides knowledge on the technical, regulatory, and practical aspects of renovating older residential buildings, particularly multi-apartment blocks. Through overall introduction of such topics as thermal performance analysis, insulation materials, HVAC systems, renewable energy integration, and digital design tools (e.g., BIM), this module equips learners with basic concepts and terminology necessary for understating of renovation needs and key measures. It is designed to prepare participants for more advanced studies in energy-efficient renovation.

Technology for residential building renovation and sustainable modernization - this course delivers comprehensive expertise in residential building renovation and building thermal performance analysis using advanced energy efficiency strategies and thermal insulation materials implementation. Students will master prefabricated insulation panels techniques, AUTOCAD applications, and HVAC system renovation methodologies for optimal solar installation integration and heating system modernization. The curriculum focuses on practical building pipe selection strategies, photogrammetry 3D capturing methods, and laser scanning technology for comprehensive 3D model creation and BIM modeling applications. Participants will gain hands-on experience with digital facade design tools, building modernization techniques, and sustainable construction practices for energy-efficient renovation projects. The program emphasizes thermal performance optimization, insulation material selection, and digital design integration for comprehensive building renovation solutions that enhance energy efficiency and sustainability in residential building modernization.
